The main problem is that the media query uses the styling for the document, not the `container` class. This means that `1em` in the query is different than `1em` in the `container` div. For example, this snippet uses the same styling for the text that the document uses, so it works. Note that I also set the body&#39;s margin to 0 because the margin of the body is also included in the media query. This solution, as I&#39;m sure you&#39;ll agree, is not the desired result.

**Not-So-Good Version**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: true console: false babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .container {
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
      max-width: 55em;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    @media screen and (max-width: 59em) {
      .container {
        margin-left: 2em;
        margin-right: 2em;
      }
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;article&gt;
          Here is a nice long paragraph which should
          certainly hit the wrap limit.
          It should do this because it is a long paragraph,
          with more words and characters than fit in the
          maximum width configured for this page.
          I have written multiple sentences in a row, to
          ensure that this will take ample screen space horizontally.
          I am good at writing like this.
        &lt;/article&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

&gt; 3. How should this goal be achieved instead?

Instead, I would recommend a flexbox. Set the `container` class style to be just

```
display: flex;
justify-content: center;
```
and move the other styling to the `content` class. Set the margin of the `content` class to `auto 2em`. (see the snippet below)

**Good Flexbox Version**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: false babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .container {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .content {
      margin: auto 2em;
      max-width: 55em;
      font-family: monospace;
      font-size: 16pt;
      line-height: 1.3;
      text-align: justify;
