Suppose `N = 546` and obtained `firstDigit = 5`. So to move firstDigit to the last position first you have to remove the firstDigit from **N**. If `count = number of digits of N` then `N - (firstDigit * 10^(count-1))` will give the number without firstDigit. For N = 546 you will get `removedFirstDigit = 46`. So then you just have to attach firstDigit to the last position using `10 * removedFirstDigit + firstDigit` to get the final answer. Follow that code for better understanding,

