Try this:

    pod &#39;podName&#39;, :git =&gt; &#39;git repo&#39;, :tag =&gt; &#39;1.5.0&#39;

If it can&#39;t find the tag, you probably has an error in your `.podspec` file inside the tagged version.

However, you would still be able to install the tag like this:

    pod &#39;podName&#39;, :git =&gt; &#39;git repo&#39;, :branch =&gt; &#39;1.5.0&#39;

You need to pass the state down to your styled components:

    &lt;ImgClust1 onClick={() =&gt; setFill(!fill)}&gt;
      ...
      &lt;TopLine fill={fill} /&gt;
      &lt;RightLine fill={fill} /&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/ImgClust1&gt;

Then `fill` will be available as props to the styled component and it can be used like this:

    const TopLine = styled.div`
      ...
      height: ${p =&gt; p.fill ? &#39;100%&#39; : &#39;1px&#39;};
    `;

or:

    const Box1 = styled.div`
      ...
      ${(p) =&gt;
        p.fill
          ? &quot; &quot;
          : `
          :hover img {
            transform: matrix(1.1, 0, 0, 1.1, 0, 0);
          }
       `}
    `;


[Adapting styled components based on props][1]


  [1]: https://www.styled-components.com/docs/basics#adapting-based-on-props

